comment_text:
The World of Walker Timeline (Originally written by me but stolen by XxTechno ShockxX and subsequently pinned):

1. Heading Home:

In a college library, a young woman comes across a book documenting an ancient tribe called the "Walkers". As she's reading, she begins to have unexplainable flashbacks about living in this tribe, and so she continues reading...

At the top of a tree, she sat looking through a monocular, through which she saw a shower of meteors piercing through the atmosphere. In a panic, she jumped from the tree and started sprinting back to the village. Soon thereafter, she located the tribe leader who was busy instructing students on how to use the Walker Drones. This being an emergency, she interrupted the lesson and showed the leader photos of the incoming meteors.

Promptly, the leader aborted the lesson, sent the drones off, and initiated a state of emergency. Various artifacts were hidden away in time capsules for the future, and the tribe descended into a bunker to wait out the long and dubious night.


2. On My Way

To make sense of her newly-found memories, the woman has been vigorously researching the Walkers. Most historians and professors are skeptical of her ideas, but she truly believes that she's on to something.

She goes on a massive world-wide hunt for clues about the Walkers when she discovers something massive: a giant Walker symbol buried underground. With the whole world watching, they excavate this symbol, and she is taken seriously for the first time.


3. Alone, Pt. II

A short time after the discovery of the Walker symbol, the woman has the attention of the whole world. But when she's not receiving awards or being interviewed, she continues to research; she must learn more.

Driven by a vague memory, she has assembled various drawings, and by vandalizing a painting in a museum, has uncovered a hidden map to something. She proceeds to travel the world searching for this location and meets a local man who knows some of the landmarks in the drawings and map.

Together they trek into the depths of a cave depicted in the drawings until the man deems it too unsafe to continue. Yet she persists, and eventually comes across an ancient ritual site used by the Walkers. In the center of the large and sunny ravine sits a giant shield-like object with the Walker symbol on it, overgrown with moss, and shortly, out of the weeds, flies multiple walker drones.


4. Alone

A call is put out, and other Walkers from all over the internet join together in different groups around the world. It is unknown if these are all members of the original Walker tribe or just fans of the woman's work.


5. Sing Me To Sleep

Some person or entity guides a group of Walkers together. They all carry some object in their backpack, that when united, projects some pattern on to the ceiling. It's possibly a Walker Drone, as the projection looks similar to those in "Darkside".


6. Tired

Many years after the re-forming of the Walkers, a solar flare is approaching fast. Groups of Walkers around the world make drones that would scan bits of ruins, and, once united, construct them into a utopia for the survivors of the flare. They also build shield-like objects that, once enough things were scanned, would guide the walkers together. They bury these underground, where they'll be safe, and all sit together as the flare hits and they presumably die.


7. Faded

One of the Walkers who survived is trying to cope with the new world after the flare. He's completely alone and trying to find a place that isn't in ruins because of the flare, guided by a picture he carries of a lovely rural house. He travels a long way, hoping this house will be his salvation, but when he gets there, it's destroyed like everything else.


8. All Falls Down

An unknown amount of time later, a group of teenagers, who presumably grew up in this post-apoplectic world, dig up one of the safes with the walker Drones but don't know what to do with them. In the night, a group of older people, presumably some of the Walkers who buried the drones in the first place, come and set something up that shows them how to use them.


9. Darkside

The group of older Walkers is scanning a monument of some sort, and the teenagers observe them doing it from afar. They are inspired, and after fiddling with the drones a bit, go and scan another monument. Finally, the Walkers officially meet on a mountaintop.


10. Diamond Heart

Different groups of Walkers discover these scanners and, soon, the shields start showing glimpses of what other scanners are scanning. The scanners proceed to guide the walkers together once again, and they finally build their utopia.
Name: Fake_A_Smile
